-- Chinese property developers shares jump after home loan rules relaxed
-- By Clare Jim
-- Thu Oct 02, 2014 10:25PM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, Oct 3 (Reuters) - Shares of Chinese property developers surged in Hong Kong on Friday after China cut mortgage rates and downpayment levels for some home buyers for the first time since the 2008 global financial crisis. [ID:nL3N0RV3IG]

The relaxation of the lending rules was announced on Tuesday. Markets in Hong Kong were closed on Wednesday and Thursday for public holidays. In early morning trade, China Vanke <2202.HK>, the country's largest residential developer, jumped 4.2 percent. Mid-sized Guangzhou R&F Properties Co Ltd <2777.HK> advanced 4.5 percent. Greentown China Holdings Ltd <3900.HK> and Sunac China Holdings Ltd <1918.HK> rose 6.2 percent and 5.6 percent respectively.